<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/25401ADKDNDVMDKDPLNQQVHNPHGRHDJGH> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "COFFEE CONCERT: Sarah Hagen";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"ItalicText\">“Why hurry over beautiful things? Why not linger and enjoy them?”</span> So pondered Clara Schumann, remembered as one of the finest pianists of all time.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In “Wonder Women!”, pianist and humorist <span class=\"BoldText\">Sarah Hagen</span> delves into the remarkable stories and piano music of forgotten female composers from the classical repertoire. This recital will highlight piano works by 18th and 19th century composers, including Clara Schumann, Cécile Chaminade, Dora Pejačević, and others. Included will be stunningly gorgeous music by Marianna Martines, who lived in the same circles as Haydn and Mozart, and often joined Mozart in piano duets at the musical soirées she and her sister held in their Viennese home.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.porttheatre.com/site/assets/files/2171/wonder_women_programme_-_nanaimo_2026.pdf\">PROGRAMME</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Mel Bonis (1858-1937): <span class=\"ItalicText\">Meditation</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Marianna Martines (1744-1812): Sonata in G major<span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Allegro brillante</span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Andante</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Allegro Assai</span> <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Fanny Mendelssohn Hensel (1805-1847): <span class=\"ItalicText\">Mélodie Op. 4 No. 2</span> 					<span><br/></span>Delphine von Scauroth (1813–1887): <span class=\"ItalicText\">Songs Without Words, Op. 18 No. 2</span> 		<span><br/></span>F. Mendelssohn Hensel: <span class=\"ItalicText\">Allegro vivace, from HN 392</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Marianne von Auenbrugger (1759-1782): from Sonata in E-flat major, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Largo</span> <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Cécile Chaminade (1857–1944): <span class=\"ItalicText\">Guitar</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Dora Pejačević (1885-1923): <span class=\"ItalicText\">Violets</span> <span><br/></span>Agathe Backer Grøndahl (1847-1907): <span class=\"ItalicText\">Song of the roses</span><span><br/></span>D. Pejačević: <span class=\"ItalicText\">Rose</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Louise Farrenc (1804-1875): <span class=\"ItalicText\">Nocturne</span><span><br/></span>Clara Schumann (1819-1896): <span class=\"ItalicText\">Nocturne Op. 6 No. 2</span><span><br/></span>Amy Beach (1867-1944): <span class=\"ItalicText\">Nocturne Op. 107</span><span><br/></span>M. Bonis: <span class=\"ItalicText\">At Dusk</span><span><br/></span>
""";
