<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/39201APPPJQSCBDBPCLLVKSNCLNHTDTRQ> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Cuban Vibes: Cuba in her Carry On";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"BoldText\">CUBAN<span><br/></span>VIBES: A SYMPHONIC FESTIVAL</span> is presented by the Vancouver Island Symphony February 12-14, 2026<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">CONDUCTOR: </span>Cosette Justo Valdés<span class=\"BoldText\"></span> With the Vancouver Island Symphony<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">GUEST ARTISTS: </span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Gramma Cathy: Joelle Rabu<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The Grand Kids: VIS Noteworthy Kids Choir, (Patricia Plumley, Choir Director)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Nico Rhodes: Music Arranger<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Gramma Cathy just came back from her super fun vacation in Cuba, and she's bursting with stories to share! She found all sorts of cool music, yummy food, and fascinating customs, and she can't wait to tell her grandkids all about her adventures! You’ll hear traditional songs from Cuba and Canada, and the musicians will have everyone singing and dancing in their seats, in no time!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">About the Show:</span> 60 minutes, relaxed audience, for Kids ages 5-10, audience participation<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In the Lobby before the show: Get your photo taken, colouring sheets for instruments. 
""";
