<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/50801AMGQRGSCDNRCKBGRSTVMLTQRTDTT> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Frozen Jr. ";
  schema:description """
	The NDSS Musical Theatre class proudly presents Frozen JR., a magical 60-minute journey  into the kingdom of Arendelle featuring beloved songs like “Let It Go,” “Do You Want to Build a Snowman?” and “For the First Time in Forever.” <span><br/></span>This heartwarming story comes to life through the talented performances of Emily Losell as Elsa, Makayla White as Anna, Erik Griffin as Kristoff, Kayla Okada as Olaf, Flynn Maher as Sven, and Vincent Ploeger as Hans. <span><br/></span>Directed by Kelly Barnum, with choreography by Sarah Keilly, musical direction by  Elizabeth Herman, and production design by Chantelle Delage, this production showcases  the creativity, dedication, and hard work of NDSS students—including beautifully crafted  sets and props from the Musical Theatre Art class. Join us this January at the Port Theatre  for a performance full of wonder, laughter, and the spirit of true connection.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
