<http://www.spektrix.com/theporttheatre/event/47602APDGJDQCRHPJKMLGSJGRTBCCHCRB> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "LEGENDS SHOW";
  schema:description """
	\"Legends Show\" brings you some of North America's most exciting performers live on stage. Accompanied by the “Rockin’ Royals Band”, this show will feature the most incredible Tributes to Hank Williams, Patsy Cline, Roy Orbison and Elvis Presley.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Hank Williams: Jeff Award-winning actor and musician, Zachary Stevenson (from Vancouver Island, BC, now residing in Chicago IL, USA) brings the “Hillbilly Shakespeare’s songs to life with his heartfelt homage to Williams’ brief but prolific career. More than a country singer, Hank Williams was an essential American voice. Recording hit songs such as \"Hey Good Lookin’,\" \"Your Cheating Heart,” \"I'm So Lonesome I Could Cry,” and many others, Hank’s spirit and influence live on in the hearts of fans all around the world.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Patsy Cline: Amberley Beatty (from Elmira, ON) will make you 'fall to pieces' with her incredible look and sound of one of  the greatest singers in the history of country music the late Patsy Cline. With the western garb, bright red lips, and the sultry sound, Amberley captures the essence of Patsy Cline like no other. You will be taken back to the 50’s with the incredible talents of Amberley.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Roy Orbison: Jesse Aron (from Wisconsin, USA), is recognized as one of USA’s top Roy Orbison Tribute performers. With his effortless voice and uncanny resemblance to Roy, Jesse will take you back in time with such hits as ‘Crying’, ‘Pretty Woman’, ‘Only The Lonely’, ‘Running Scared’, and many more of your favourites.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Elvis Presley: Pete Paquette (from Toronto, ON) is a multi-award winning Elvis Tribute Artist. Known for captivating his audiences through his incredible voice, high energy, charisma, and playful spontaneity. With hits such as Jailhouse Rock, Suspicious Minds, Don’t Be Cruel, Can’t Help Falling In Love, and many more, Pete’s Tribute to the King of Rock and Roll will leave you wanting more. 
""";
